column1: As #COVID19 cases rise there is an urgent need for blood & plasma donations.   If you are healthy not at risk & are interesting in donating to help #COVID19 patients more info can be found here: https://t.co/hp2QRwKFR4

Con el número de casos de #COVID19 creciendo todos podemos hacer que este Día de Acción de Gracias sea más seguro.   Haga su parte: 1) Quédese en casa si puede. 2) pongase su mascarilla sobre su boca Y nariz. 3) Manténgase 6 pies de los demás. 4) Lávese las manos. https://t.co/zmvu5Tc8DM

With the number of #COVID19 cases continuing to increase we can all make #Thanksgiving safer.   Do your part to slow the spread: 1) Stay home if you can. 2) Wear a mask over your mouth AND nose. 3) Stay 6ft from others & avoid crowds. 4) Wash your hands often. https://t.co/8wTvlCzk0a

Latinos are disproportionately impacted by #COVID19. Now more than ever it’s crucial to #GetCovered.   Between Nov. 1 through Jan. 31:  ✅Update your coverage  ✅Change health insurance providers  ✅Renew your plans   Visit https://t.co/acdJdL6h9b to explore your options!

Happy to see the @USGSA has officially began the Presidential transition giving the Biden transition team access to key resources including critical info on the ongoing #COVID19 pandemic to help get this virus under control. https://t.co/JnyR0TOYCx

More than 245000 Americans have died of #COVID19 & cases are surging in all 50 states.  This wave is threatening the health & economic well-being of our entire country. We must act now to pass another relief package & deliver the help Americans desperately need. https://t.co/fBp45mvVEi

Last week I introduced the bipartisan Fly Safe & Healthy Act to help prevent the spread of #COVID19 among air travelers by creating a pilot program to conduct #temperaturechecks at @TSA checkpoints.  This is one way to help promote safety as more people begin to travel.

All 3 counties in #CA24 are now in the most restrictive purple #COVID19 tier meaning the virus is widespread.  As we approach Thanksgiving & the holiday season it's recommended that you only celebrate w/ your immediate household in order to slow the spread of this virus.

#COVID19 jeopardizes decades of progress and U.S. investment in global child health and survival. We must work together to make sure gains made are not lost. This #ChildHealthWeek let’s pave a new and better way forward for children everywhere.

As #COVID19 cases rise w/ a million in just the last week it’s clear we’re entering a new phase of this virus.   We must take care of our communities & provide additional relief w/ stimulus checks rent/mortgage relief testing & tracing small biz relief & local gov support.

Applications for the Coronavirus Food Assistance Program 2.0 are now open! CFAP 2.0 provides assistance for agricultural producers impacted by #COVID19. The @USDA is accepting applications now through Dec. 11 2020.  Learn more here: https://t.co/cYyhLfLfjg https://t.co/sOwJ7dfUuv

During the #COVID19 pandemic having access to affordable quality health coverage is more important than ever. Don’t go uncovered. Go to https://t.co/acdJdL6h9b and find a quality affordable plan that works for you.  And please remember to #WearAMask https://t.co/K2Ab3otONw

#CA24 veterans: ahead of Veteran's Day this week the #SLOVeteransServiceCollaborative is hosting a virtual resource fair to provide different local resources on health employment housing & more.  All webinars will be held virtually via zoom due to #COVID19. Learn more here: https://t.co/l9GHX7tuIs

The US has hit 10M #COVID19 cases & is breaking records each day. I’m one of these cases but luckily I only experienced mild symptoms. Not everyone is so lucky.   That's why this somber milestone is beyond unacceptable & reflects a complete lack of leadership by the Trump Admin. https://t.co/sDGwewGfS6

Together we will take decisive action on #COVID19 make overdue investments in our infrastructure protect & expand the ACA protect our planet from climate change & create good-paying jobs in the renewable energy sector while we’re at it.

The #COVID19 pandemic is fueling the housing crisis.   Millions of Americans are facing eviction even during a pandemic.   #KnowYourRights. Find out if you qualify for protection from eviction.   Visit https://t.co/v30N7gNnvO for more information.

Good news in our ongoing fight to tackle #COVID19 & expand testing & contact tracing. Our communities have received a total of $16.8 million in grants from the #PPP  & Health Care Enhancement Act which'll help public health officials get #COVID19 under control in our community. https://t.co/zjghcxVsy8

Thank you for all the well wishes during my journey with #COVID19. I'm happy to report I was cleared by my doctors to leave quarantine & I'm so excited to be back on the beautiful #CentralCoast.   Please remember to take all the necessary precautions to keep each other safe. https://t.co/VtSU8aUvw8

Today is #WorldFoodDay & @FAO is highlighting the ways that we can preserve access to safe & nutritious food even in a global pandemic.  Proud to have worked with my Republican colleague @RepDonBacon to ensure our children have access to nutritious school meals during #COVID19.

Thank you again for all the well wishes since being diagnosed with #COVID19. My symptoms have included fatigue body aches fever loss of appetite & chills but I'm feeling better. This illness is no joke.  Remember to #WearAMask & social distance. I hope to be back in CA soon. https://t.co/PUebtStOxL

A survey of CA farmworkers found that #COVID19 has made these essential workers fearful of seeking medical help & of their long-term financial security.  Our farmworkers are vital to our communities & must be given the resources needed to stay healthy & get through this pandemic. https://t.co/b8tiJc2W2E

.@California_HCD is receiving $550 million in #CARESAct funding to purchase or rehabilitate hotels motels & vacant apartment buildings to convert them into long-term affordable housing.  This funding will help CA address the ongoing housing shortage during #COVID19.
Thank you so much for the outpouring of well wishes after my recent #COVID19 diagnosis. I hope to be back on the Central Coast as soon as I can.
After experiencing mild symptoms I was instructed to take another test today and have tested positive for COVID-19.   My full statement: https://t.co/Da8quSJTAV https://t.co/z9JqqJkscx

My thoughts are with the President and the First Lady as they begin treatment for their recent #COVID19 diagnosis.  I hope this situation serves as a reminder to our nation to continue to follow health guidelines wear a mask & socially distance.

A powerful message from my friend & former Santa Barbara County Fire Chief Eric Peterson. We should take his advice to keep our community safe & healthy by wearing masks & following social distancing guidelines. We all have a part to play to prevent the spread of #COVID19.

Since #COVID19 began there's been an increase in reports of hate crimes & racist incidents against those of Asian descent.  Racism is never acceptable. I'm proud to stand with the Asian community & vote today with my colleagues to condemn all forms of anti-Asian sentiment.
